HEADWORD: Oke
<hw>Oke</hw> <pr>(⟦omac⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Turk.
<ets>okkah</ets>, fr. Ar. <ets>⟦umac⟧k⟦imac⟧yah</ets>,
<ets>wak⟦imac⟧yah</ets>, prob. fr. Gr. <grk>o'yggi`a</grk>,
<grk>o'ygki`a</grk>, an ounce, fr. L. <ets>uncia</ets>. Cf.
<er>Ounce</er> a weight.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A Turkish and Egyptian
weight, equal to about 2⟦frac34⟧ pounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An Hungarian and Wallachian measure, equal to about
2⟦frac12⟧ pints.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

